This paper discusses the distribution of blame and responsibility in accidents involving semi-autonomous cars, which involves the intersection of artificial intelligence (AI), human-computer interaction (HCI), robotics (RO), machine learning (LG), and systems and control (SY). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.AI, followed by cs.HC, as the paper also considers the role of human drivers in shared control scenarios. The paper also discusses the technical aspects of semi-autonomous cars, which falls under cs.RO and cs.SY, and the use of machine learning algorithms, which falls under cs.LG.
